"de Viron O., Dehant V., Goosse H., Crucifix M.","Effect of global warming on the length-of-day",2002,"Geophysical Research Letters","29","7",,"50","1",,,,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-0036555088&partnerID=40&md5=42ab645dfd7bc7b021ccc7820ab31791","Observatoire Royal de Belgique, Avenue Circulare, 3, Brussels 1180, Belgium","de Viron, O., Observatoire Royal de Belgique, Avenue Circulare, 3, Brussels 1180, Belgium; Dehant, V., Observatoire Royal de Belgique, Avenue Circulare, 3, Brussels 1180, Belgium; Goosse, H., Observatoire Royal de Belgique, Avenue Circulare, 3, Brussels 1180, Belgium; Crucifix, M., Observatoire Royal de Belgique, Avenue Circulare, 3, Brussels 1180, Belgium","The anthropogenic increase in greenhouse gas concentrations in the Earth atmosphere will probably induce important modifications of the global circulation in the atmosphere and ocean. Due to the angular momentum conservation of the Earth atmosphere-ocean system, variation of the length-of-day (LOD) can be expected. By using the outputs of the models participating to the Coupled Model Intercomparison Project (CMIP-2), we reach the following conclusions: (1) the models globally agree to an increase of the LOD of the order of 1 μs/year, (2) the effect is mostly associated with an increase of the mean zonal wind, of which about one third is compensated by a change in mass repartition.",,"Earth atmosphere; Gases; Global circulation; Global warming; angular momentum; atmospheric circulation; day length; global warming; greenhouse gas; zonal wind",,,,,,"Barthelet, P., Terray, L., Valcke, S., Transient CO2 experiment using the ARPEGE/OPAlCE nonflux corrected coupled model (1998) Geophys. Res. Let, 25, pp. 2277-2280; Boer, G.J., Flato, G., Ramsden, D., A transient climate change simulation with greenhouse gas and aerosol forcing: Projected climate to the twenty-first century (2000) Climate Dyn, 16, pp. 427-450; Boville, B.A., Gent, P.R., The NCAR climate system model (1998) J. Cl